# Secrets — never commit actual secret MATERIAL.
# LESSON: scope to value-bearing files, NOT resource definitions or docs that merely
# contain the word "secret" (e.g. k8s ExternalSecret / ClusterSecretStore manifests).
# A broad `*secret*` glob will silently swallow legit resource defs.
*.env
.env
*.key
*.pem
*.plain.yaml
secrets.plain.*
secrets.dec.*
age-key.txt
auth-profiles.json

# Terraform / OpenTofu — state & local working dirs may carry secrets; never commit.
# NOTE: this ignores STATE and TFVARS, never the .tf source or config.example/ JSON —
# those are the deliverable and must stay tracked.
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.tfvars
!*.tfvars.example
*.tfplan
crash.log

# Live config directory — operator's real values (copied from config.example/).
terraform/config/

# Template-tuning artifact — NOT part of the deliverable, never ship it.
_TEMPLATE-FRICTION-LOG.md

# Local / OS
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Rendered diagram exports (sources stay in markdown)
# docs/diagrams/*.png
# docs/diagrams/*.svg
